v1.29.0 - task dependencies (blocked-by edges with cycle detection)

Schema: new TaskDependency edge (taskId, dependsOnId, type) with cuid id,
denormalised teamId, FK CASCADE on both endpoints, unique (taskId,
dependsOnId), indexes on teamId and dependsOnId. New DependencyType enum
(FINISH_TO_START + RELATES_TO) and new NotifyType value TASK_UNBLOCKED.
Migration is additive + backfills task.manage_dependencies on every system
Manager role.

Service: BFS reachability cycle check before insert (409 DEPENDENCY_CYCLE),
self-loop / cross-team / cross-project guards, status guard wired into
tasksService.update + reorder, post-DONE unblock notification fan-out to
assignee + technician, blocker-count map for kanban lists.

Routes: GET/POST/DELETE under
/api/teams/:teamId/projects/:projectId/tasks/:taskId/dependencies.
Writes gated by the new task.manage_dependencies permission.

Frontend: Dependencies section on TaskDetailPage with picker + inline
cycle error; kanban card lock badge driven by incompleteBlockerCount on
TaskView; admin Settings -> Preferences toggle for the
tasks.dependencyEnforcement InstanceSetting (off / warn / block). EN +
FA i18n strings.

Tests: 13 new integration tests cover cycle / self-loop / cross-team /
duplicate / both-directions GET / status guard block + warn + off /
unblock notification / multi-blocker / FK cascade / DELETE / member-
without-permission 403. Updated roles permissions catalog count
(14 -> 15). Full suite 247 passed, 5 skipped (LDAP-only).

Webhook events: task.dependency_added / task.dependency_removed.
Activity-log entries via logActivity.